<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Photovoltaic Spandrel Market</h2>    <p>The photovoltaic spandrel market faces several key challenges that can hinder its growth and adoption. One major challenge is the <strong>high Initial Costs</strong> associated with the installation of photovoltaic spandrels. Although costs have been decreasing over time, the upfront investment remains a barrier for many construction projects.</p>    <p>Additionally, the <strong>Integration into Building Design</strong> poses difficulties. Architects and builders often struggle to incorporate photovoltaic spandrels aesthetically without compromising on the overall design or functionality of the building.</p>    <p>The <strong>Regulatory Hurdles</strong> present another challenge. Strict building codes and local ordinances can limit the adoption of photovoltaic spandrel technologies, creating complications for developers trying to innovate within existing frameworks.</p>    <p>Lastly, there is a <strong>Lack of Awareness</strong> among stakeholders regarding the benefits and potential applications of photovoltaic spandrels. This lack of education can result in underutilization of the technology, impacting overall market growth.</p>        <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Photovoltaic Spandrel Market</h2>    <p>Despite the challenges, there are several emerging growth opportunities within the photovoltaic spandrel market. The <strong>Increasing Demand for Sustainable Building Solutions</strong> is one of the primary drivers of growth. As construction practices lean towards sustainability, the adoption of photovoltaic spandrels can be promoted as a viable solution to meet energy efficiency guidelines.</p>    <p>The rise of <strong>Smart Building Technologies</strong> also opens up avenues for innovation. As more buildings are equipped with IoT devices and advanced energy management systems, photovoltaic spandrels can easily integrate into these systems, enhancing their energy-pro